<title>Job Bank  Questionnaire- Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">


<CENTER>

<table border=10><tr><td valign="top">
<h2><center>The Heritage Foundation<br>
Job Bank</center></h2>
</td></tr></table>
</center><p>
This is a Microsoft Word form document.  It is compatible with both Windows and Macintosh operating systems running Microsoft Word.
 
 <p>If you use another word processing package you may not be able to open the form.  If that is the case, you will want to <b>save the Adobe Acrobat version</b> of the form, print it out and mail it in with your resume. For mailing address and fax number, <a href="app.html#mail">click here</a>.  If you do not have a copy of Acrobat, you can download it for free at: <a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/">http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/</a>


<p>


<table border cellpadding=10>
<caption align=center><h3>Job Bank Questionnaire</h3></caption>
<tr align=center>
<th width=20%><a href="question.pdf">Adobe Acrobat <i>(272K)</i></a></th> <th width=40% cellspacing=10><a href="question.exe">Windows <i>(41K)</i></a></th> <th width=40%><a href="question.sea">Macintosh <i>(46K)</i></a></th> </tr>
 <tr><td valign="top" width=160>To download the questionnaire for Adobe Acrobat, click on the link, and save the file (question.pdf) to your hard drive. Using Adobe Acrobat software, you can then read and print the questionnaire on any PC.  If you do not have a copy of Acrobat, you can download it for free at: <a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/">http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/.</a></td>

<td valign="top" width=160 cellspacing=10>To download the questionnaire, click on the link, and save the self-extracting Zip file (question.exe) to a directory on your hard drive. In File Manager, double click on question.exe, and two files--form1b.doc and readme.txt--will be created in the directory where question.exe was originally downloaded. Open "form1.doc" in your word processing program.</td>
<td valign="top" width=160>To download the questionnaire, a self-extracting file, click on the link and save the file (question.sea) to your hard disk.  Double click on the new icon: a Microsoft Word form will be created.</td>
</tr><tr><td><b><a href="question.pdf">Download</a> Questionnaire for Adobe Acrobat</td>
<td><b><a href="question.exe">Download</a> Questionnaire for Windows</a></b></td>

<td><b><a href="question.sea">Download</a> Questionnaire for Macintosh</a></b></td></tr>
</table><p>
</center><b>Questionnaire Instructions</b><p>

This form is fairly self-explanatory.  There are just a few things you need to know before you fill it out:<ol>

 <p><li>This is a Microsoft Word form document.  It is compatible with both Windows and Macintosh operating systems running Microsoft Word.
 
 <p><li>If you use another word processing package you may not be able to open the form.  If that is the case, you will want to save the Adobe Acrobat version of the form, print it out and mail it in with your resume. For mailing address and fax number, <a href="app.html#mail">click here</a>.  If you do not have a copy of Acrobat, you can download it for free at: <a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/">http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/</a>
 
 
 <p><li>To move your cursor from one answer blank to another, <b>DO NOT HIT RETURN</b> (it will disrupt formatting).  Use the tab, arrow key or mouse to travel from field to field.
 
 <p><li>Certain answer blanks/check boxes will give you <b>help instructions</b> in the bottom scroll bar when you tab to that field.  Please note that some sections are optional, such as a second undergraduate degree.
 
 <p><li>Please be sure to spell-check your document.
 
 <p><li>Save the form as a Microsoft Word document, entitling it with your last name and first initial (or as much as you can fit if you do not have a Macintosh or Windows 95).
 
 <p><li>To send the form to us via e-mail, either select "send" under the file menu in Word, or follow the instructions of your e-mail software concerning how you should send/attach files to e-mail messages.
 
 <p><li>Please send us your resume in a Microsoft Word compatible file format or as an Adobe Acrobat (.pdf) file.  Send it as a separate file in the same e-mail message as your Job Placement Information Form.
 
 <p><li><b>E-mail your Information Sheet and resume to: jobbank@heritage.org</b>.</ol>
 <p>
<a name="mail">If you need to send either your resume or questionnaire via regular mail, please send it to:<blockquote>

Ms. Kristin Ganong<br>
Job Bank Coordinator<br>
The Heritage Foundation<br>
214 Massachusetts Avenue, N.E.<br>
Washington, D.C.  20002<br>
Fax: (202) 675-1778
</blockquote>
